==Old English==
===Spellings===
ġebed, ''occasionally in combinations'' bed
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bed-'' ‘prayer, entreaty’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[bede]], Old Saxon [[beda]] (Dutch [[bede]]), Old High German [[beta]], [[gibet]] (German [[Gebet]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐌹𐌳𐌰]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /je'bed/

===Noun===
'''ġebed''' ''n''
# a [[prayer]], a religious observance
#:''Hie to gebede feollon'': they fell to prayer.  (Cædmon’s ''Metrical Paraphrase'')


